cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IT

This paper is about face recognition using sparse representations. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper deals with image analysis and recognition. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a new model for face recognition. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper uses a probabilistic graphical model framework to mine conditional dependencies between sparse local features. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper deals with image and video analysis. The fifth likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper proposes a new approach to overcome the misalignment problem in face recognition.
